Due to the below, I think it's the better method.
With the scorched earth method.

There are less calls to the itemListAdapter
if the app crashed, goes wrong, etc, it doesn't effect anything, it only writes once everything is done, and it's quite fast.
less function calls, calling deleteItem will call multiple functions that aren't needed until the end.
For example updateThumbnailUrl() doesn't need to be called each time, only at the end.

